{"lemma":"مَوْجُودٌ","slug":"مَوْجُودٌ","root":"#.ج.د","root_slug":"_-ج-د","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ج-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41699"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"existing"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"available"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"found"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of وَجَدَ (wajada, “to find”)."},"ipa":["/maw.d͡ʒuːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41699","headword_ar":"مَوْجُودٌ","root":"wjd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wujida","text_ar":"وُجِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"existing; come to pass:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K:) or, as an irreg. pass. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awojadahu","text_ar":"اَوْجَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused to be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exist;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to come to pass; brought into existence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawojuwdaAtN","text_ar":"مَوْجُودَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": which is a term applied to three kinds of things: namely, that which exists and has neither beginning nor end; and such is only God: that which exists and has a beginning and an end; as the substances of the present world: and that which exists and has a beginning but no end; as men in the world to come. (TA.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Present."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawojuwdN","text_ar":"مَوْجُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"within one's power; over which one has power."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%85%D9%88%D8%AC%D9%88%D8%AF/","headword_ar":"موجود","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23775#663c3d","body_html":"<span>الموجود: هو مبدأ الآثار، ومظهر الأحكام في الخارج، وحدد الحكماء الموجود بأنه الذي يمكن أن يخبر عنه، والمعدوم بنقيضه، وهو ما لا يمكن أن يخبر عنه.</span>"}]}}